caption: Welcome home, bison!From Elk Island National Park to Banff National Park, the bison are now home again among the mountains. After being absent from the wild for over a century, their homecoming is a historic and cultural triumph.For months, the bison will remain in an enclosed pasture in the Panther Valley, closely monitored by Parks Canada. In approximately June , the herd will be released to elore the full ~1200km2 reintroduction zone in the remote eastern slopes of Banff where they will interact with other native species, forage for food and fulfill their missing role in the ecosystem.
